        "Stochastic amounts split into four causes: credit-related (uncertainty from default/recovery events), behavioral (a counterparty's own decision, e.g. exercising a prepayment or withdrawal option), indexed/contingent (driven by a market variable, e.g. a floating-rate coupon), and new-business (cash flows from contracts not yet signed, e.g. next quarter's expected new loans and deposits)."
